  ./COVERAGE.md:536:| `io.micrometer:context-propagation` | [1.1.0<br>- 1.2.1](metadata/io.micrometer/context-propagation/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Micrometer Context Propagation captures and restores contextual data across boundaries such as ThreadLocal values, Reactor Context, and other context carrier mechanisms. It provides a small set of accessors, registries, snapshots, and executor wrappers so libraries and applications can propagate request or tracing context consistently across asynchronous execution.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.micrometer/context-propagation/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:537:| `io.micrometer:micrometer-commons` | [1.14.4<br>- 1.17.0](metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-commons/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Micrometer Commons provides shared utility code used by Micrometer projects, including common conventions, logging helpers, diagnostics, and context utilities. It is a support module that other Micrometer components depend on rather than an end-user metrics backend or registry.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.micrometer/micrometer-commons/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:538:| `io.micrometer:micrometer-jakarta9` | [1.16.5<br>- 1.17.0](metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-jakarta9/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Micrometer Jakarta 9 provides Micrometer instrumentation support for Jakarta EE 9+ APIs, including Jakarta JMS and Jakarta Mail. It lets JVM applications observe these Jakarta-based components through Micrometer meters and observations.</details> | [100.0% (8/8 calls)](stats/io.micrometer/micrometer-jakarta9/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:539:| `io.micrometer:micrometer-observation` | [1.14.4<br>- 1.17.0](metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-observation/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Micrometer Observation provides APIs for creating and propagating observations that can be transformed into metrics, traces, and logs across instrumentation code. It supplies observation contexts, handlers, predicates, filters, conventions, and scopes so libraries and applications can instrument operations independently of a specific monitoring backend.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.micrometer/micrometer-observation/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:540:| `io.micrometer:micrometer-registry-prometheus` | [1.16.5<br>- 1.17.0](metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-registry-prometheus/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Micrometer Registry Prometheus provides a MeterRegistry implementation that exports Micrometer metrics through Prometheus using the Prometheus Java Client 1.x stack. It lets JVM applications collect metrics with Micrometer and expose scrape data for Prometheus-compatible monitoring systems.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.micrometer/micrometer-registry-prometheus/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:541:| `io.micrometer:micrometer-tracing` | [1.7.0](metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-tracing/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Micrometer Tracing is a facade over tracing concepts for JVM applications. It provides APIs for spans, tracers, baggage, context propagation, and integrations that let applications instrument distributed traces without depending directly on a specific tracing backend.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.micrometer/micrometer-tracing/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:542:| `io.micrometer:micrometer-tracing-bridge-otel` | [1.7.0](metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-tracing-bridge-otel/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Micrometer Tracing Bridge OTel adapts Micrometer Tracing's facade to OpenTelemetry, letting applications create and propagate traces through OpenTelemetry APIs and SDK components. It provides Micrometer implementations for tracers, spans, baggage, propagation, and observation handlers backed by OpenTelemetry.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.micrometer/micrometer-tracing-bridge-otel/) |
